      <hedline>
        <hl1>Orthodox Viewpoints: Can They All Be Right?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cedarhurst Business Improvement District treasurer Ivan Greenberg letter on August 27 letter responding to August 20 article on Long Island's Orthodox Jews notes parking meters in Five Towns operate on Saturdays and Sundays (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In response to the Aug. 27 letter ''Building the Five Towns Through Mutual Respect'': Parking meters on Central Avenue and all side streets are in operation on Saturdays and Sundays.</p>
        <p>IVAN GREENBERG  Treasurer, Cedarhurst Business  Improvement District</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
